linsync (1.9.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Completes the previously-deferred roadmap niceties.
  * Image: animated GIF/APNG/WebP frame-by-frame compare (--image-frames
    first|all, default first); Radiance HDR and OpenEXR decode (tone-mapped to
    RGBA8); decoded color-type metadata on every result.
  * Document/OCR: word-level positional data via an optional, backward-compatible
    word_positions plugin-protocol field, parsed from Tesseract TSV.
  * Plugins: per-profile enable/disable override map (profile > global >
    default) threaded into prediffer/virtualizer routing, with a GUI toggle and
    a /profiles/active/plugin-enabled bridge endpoint; overlapping-prediffer
    conflict policy (--prediffer-conflict-policy chain|first-wins|last-wins).
  * Reports: image and document results round-trip as versioned JSON
    (compare --save-result <-> report --from-json) with metadata HTML reports.
  * Fixes ImageCompareMode::Tolerance serialization (struct variant).

 -- VisorCraft LLC <licensing@visorcraft.com>  Tue, 02 Jun 2026 13:00:00 -0500

linsync (1.8.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Feature release completing roadmap Phases 4-10.
  * Performance: lazy windowed rendering for large text diffs and large folder
    comparisons (the view never loads an unbounded diff/tree at once); paged
    core APIs and bridge endpoints (/compare/text/window, /folder/query with
    sort/filter/state/paging).
  * Specialized engines: rendered document compare (pdftoppm) with
    --document-pages range selection; webpage rendered/screenshot compare via
    an out-of-process Qt WebEngine renderer plus a filterable resource tree;
    archive compare via unpacker/virtualizer plugins with nested-archive
    recursion and member extraction; table date/time tolerance and per-column
    case/trim/regex rules.
  * Plugins: option-schema validation and an option/enabled store; install and
    remove across core/CLI/GUI; first-run trust prompt; per-profile prediffer
    routing and prediffer chaining; sandbox-confinement reporting and
    per-plugin diagnostics.
  * Merge: interactive Git mergetool that launches the GUI and validates the
    saved output; conflict highlight/scroll by per-side line numbers.
  * Reports: versioned save-result/from-json for text/folder/table/binary;
    --relative-paths portable reports; preview-before-export.
  * Sessions/projects: multi-tab session persistence and restore; CLI session
    and project commands; per-entry compare profiles; recent-workspaces list;
    persist-recent-paths privacy control.
  * Accessibility: screen-reader status/error announcements and high-contrast
    diff change bars. Localization: runtime QTranslator plus the
    lupdate/lrelease string-catalog pipeline.
  * Folder: extended-attribute (xattr) comparison mode.

 -- VisorCraft LLC <licensing@visorcraft.com>  Tue, 02 Jun 2026 12:00:00 -0500

linsync (1.8.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Correctness, security, and robustness hardening release.
  * Folder sync: fix delete operations, which previously always failed
    without removing or trashing anything.
  * Three-way merge: resolve from structured conflict regions instead of
    re-parsing marker text (content that looks like a conflict marker no
    longer corrupts the result), preserve CRLF/CR line endings on save, and
    write output atomically (temp+rename, O_NOFOLLOW).
  * Plugin sandbox: grant helpers read-only access to $HOME, apply fd/proc
    rlimits on the bubblewrap fallback, and block the full set of
    credential-changing syscalls.
  * Image compare: bound decoder memory and dimensions (decompression-bomb
    guard) and fix an overlay-buffer integer overflow.
  * Settings and sessions preserve unknown JSON keys across load/save.
  * OCR language selection now reaches the extractor plugin.
  * Further fixes across table, filter, trash, webpage, CLI argument parsing,
    and the GUI bridge (comma-containing folder paths, merge conflict count,
    plugin options dialog, perceptual deltaE scaling, and plugin-id
    path-traversal hardening).

